<kml>

<concept name=Guard>
<superconcept name=Military-Task>

<definition>

  A security action to fix an enemy ground force before it can
  engage the main body
  
</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is guarding the
     <slot>object</slot>
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=object>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is being guarded by the
     <slot>agent</slot>
  </slotdescription>
  
</requiredslotlist>

  <comment>
  The <slot>agent</slot> and the <slot>object</slot> have the same 
  <slot>allegiance</slot>
  </comment>

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Screen>
    Screen is also a security action.  Screen primarily provides early
    warning to a protected force.
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


